	<owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/biopharma/ExampleOfPSOAClassLevelClassificationInApplicationOntology/">
		<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">Example Of PSOA Class Level Classification In Application Ontology</rdfs:label>
		<dcterms:abstract>This example mapping ontology demonstrates an application-level implementation in which selected planned process classes are aligned to PSOA levels through class-level SubClassOf axioms using the relation prescribed by. The mappings reflect industry member knowledge about how these process types are treated within a particular recipe modeling environment. In this file, CellLineDevelopment is treated at the RecipeProcess level; CaptureStep, CloneSelectionProcess, DiafiltrationProcess, DrugProductFormulationProcess, HarvestingProcess, PolishingProcess, ProductionCultureProcess, SeedTrain, and ViralClearance are treated at the RecipeProcessStage level; and CellBanking, CentrifugationProcess, ChromatographyProcess, DilutionProcess, FiltrationProcess, PoolingProcess, and ThawingProcess are treated at the RecipeProcessOperation level. The ontology illustrates how recipe process element occurrence-based utility classification classes can be used to make the applicable PSOA level visible in the inferred hierarchy. These mappings are application-level semantic commitments rather than global definitions of the planned process classes. Although informed by a general-recipe perspective, no general recipe is implemented in this file. The example focuses on class-level typing as one possible application pattern, with additional examples planned for individual-level typing and recipe-based class extensions. Guidance on the use of recipe process element occurrence-based utility classes is also being prepared to support consistent application and interpretation of this pattern.</dcterms:abstract>
		<dcterms:contributor>Adlane Rebai, Millipore Sigma</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Ana Nikolov, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Boonserm Kulvatunyou, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Cameron Gibbs, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Gabriela Henning, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Marie-Aude Coutouly, Millipore Sigma</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Melissa Weller, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Milos Drobnjakovic, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Stephen J. Granite, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Stephen Kahmann, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:license rdf:datatype="&xsd;anyURI">http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT</dcterms:license>
		<dcterms:title>Biopharmaceutical Manufacturing Industry Council (BMIC) Example Of PSOA Class Level Classification In Application Ontology</dcterms:title>
		<owl:imports rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/biopharma/RecipeProcessOccurrenceClassificationUtility/"/>
		<owl:imports rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/biopharma/BiopharmaManufacturingExecution/"/>
		<owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/202601/biopharma/ExampleOfPSOAClassLevelClassificationInApplicationOntology/"/>
		<iof-av:copyright>Copyright (c) 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025, 2026 Open Applications Group</iof-av:copyright>
		<iof-av:maturity rdf:resource="&iof-ind;Released"/>
	</owl:Ontology>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&iof-construct;CaptureStep">
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&iof-construct;prescribedBy"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&iof-construct;RecipeProcessStage"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
	</owl:Class>
	
